CHOLERA - TANZANIA (02)
***********************
[see: Cholera - Tanzania 970506103811]
Date: Sat, 31 May 1997
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: BBC, Wed, 28 May 1997

The British Broadcasting Corporation, using a report from Radio Tanzania,
carried news of 77 deaths in an outbreak of cholera in the Kilwa and Liwale
districts of the Lindi Region in southeastern Tanzania. At least 676 cases
are confirmed by hospital admissions. This outbreak is in addition to one
in the capital, Dar es Salaam, where 115 people have died.
